  "commentary": "With SPX at 6555.15 sitting between max negative gamma at 6550 (-21.4B) and max positive gamma at 6580 (+6.6B), dealers are likely buying this dip aggressively as they're short gamma and forced to chase momentum. The massive negative GEX wall cluster from 6530-6550 (totaling -69B) creates a powerful amplification zone where any selling pressure will force dealers to sell more, potentially driving price lower with momentum. However, if we can reclaim and hold above 6580, dealers flip to selling rallies which should provide resistance.\n\nWatch 6550 as the critical inflection point - a break below triggers cascading dealer selling into the negative GEX cluster, while a bounce back above 6580 shifts dealers to resistance mode.\n\nBottom line: expect violent swings with downside acceleration if we break 6550, but strong resistance if we reach 6580.",
